In a statement, Supkem, through its chairman Hassan ole Naado, welcomed the deal and assured the Gulf states that the entire global community looks up to and counts on them to ensure that the agreement translates into tangible action to ensure peaceful coexistence.
“We are delighted that the end of the blockade and boycott restores the cordial relationships that had existed between the two brotherly neighbours,” Mr ole Naado said, referring to the Saudi Arabia and Qatar.



